From b051609922015107c4f88ef1b0fcc551af43524b Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: GitHub Pages Fix <fix@ai-verse.dev>
Date: Wed, 6 May 2026 07:40:27 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] fix: repair GitHub Pages deployment

Three bugs were preventing the site from deploying:

1. vite.config.ts imported '@vitejs/plugin-react-swc' which is not
   listed in package.json devDependencies. This caused the Vite build
   to crash immediately (17s failure). Removed vite.config.ts since
   vite.config.js already has the correct setup (uses '@vitejs/plugin-react'
   and sets base: '/ai-verse/').

2. static.yml was listening on branch 'main' but the default branch is
   'master', so the workflow never triggered on push. Fixed to 'master'.

3. deploy.yml used peaceiris/actions-gh-pages without the required
   'permissions: contents: write' block, and conflicted with static.yml.
   Removed deploy.yml in favour of the modern actions/deploy-pages approach.

Also added public/404.html + inline script in index.html to handle
SPA client-side routing on GitHub Pages (prevents hard-reload 404s).
---
 .github/workflows/deploy.yml | 28 ----------------------------
 .github/workflows/static.yml |  2 +-
 index.html                   | 10 ++++++++++
 public/404.html              | 18 ++++++++++++++++++
 vite.config.ts               |  8 --------
 5 files changed, 29 insertions(+), 37 deletions(-)
 delete mode 100644 .github/workflows/deploy.yml
 create mode 100644 public/404.html
 delete mode 100644 vite.config.ts

